# DCENT_OS first-boot SSH grace marker.
#
# This file is consumed once by /etc/init.d/S50dropbear on the FIRST boot
# of a freshly-installed image. When present:
#   1. S50dropbear stamps /data/dcent/.ssh-enabled so dropbear can come up.
#   2. S99upgrade soft-passes its SSH:22 health check.
#   3. The marker is deleted so the next boot re-engages the W1.1
#      default-credential lockdown.
#
# The grace flag breaks the circular failure flagged by the 2026-05-15
# DevOps Q1 report (finding 4K):
#   - S50dropbear refuses to start until the dashboard wizard completes.
#   - S99upgrade refuses to clear upgrade_stage until SSH:22 is up.
#   - Without grace, every fresh install would auto-revert on the second
#     power cycle because the operator had no way to finish the wizard.
#
# To rebuild a sysupgrade image WITHOUT the grace flag (paranoid lab
# mode), delete this file from the rootfs-overlay before running
# Buildroot.
#
# The dashboard wizard at http://<miner-ip>/ remains the operator's
# hard credential gate; this file ONLY gates the first boot.
